There are few greater simple joys than a nice glass of chocolate milk. While in the winter we run to the cosy embrace of a mug of hot chocolate, as temperatures rise, we need a different way to get our choccy fix. Enter hot chocolate ice cubes. These are exactly as they sound – hot chocolate in ice cube form. You can add these to a glass of cold milk and voila: a delicious summer treat. Here’s how to make them. How to make hot chocolate ice cubes For more tasty recipes for kids and grownups to enjoy, head to my Instagram, @squashedpickle. Do you have a story to share? Get in touch by emailing MetroLifestyleTeam@Metro.co.uk. MORE : Kid-friendly recipes: An easy chicken pot pie for when you don’t know what to make for dinner MORE : Kid-friendly recipes: Try these two-ingredient frozen strawberry kisses for a dreamy summer snack MORE : Kid-friendly recipes: Fro-yo blueberry sticks for summer days